        h3 Workers
        p Shown here is the number of people working in each district. Since part-time work is common in Switzerland, this statistic considers the equivalent number of full-time workers for each district.
        p An interesting observation is that many people work in Altstadt Grossbasel and Vorst√§dte, which are districts with a lower than average population. This implies that many people work in the city centre but live somewhere else.
